# {{ project_name }} — Agent Guide

## Commands

All Python commands run via `uv run`, Django commands from `src/`:

- Dev server: `cd src && uv run python manage.py runserver`
- Migrations: `cd src && uv run python manage.py makemigrations && uv run python manage.py migrate`
- Tests: `uv run pytest` (fast suite; e2e excluded by marker)
- Lint: `make lint` (ruff + import-linter layering contract) — Format: `uv run ruff format .`
- Types: `uv run mypy src/`
{% if use_celery %}- Celery: `cd src && uv run celery -A config worker -l info`
{% endif %}

## Architecture (enforced — violations fail `make lint`: ruff TID251 flags upward imports from data/ in-editor; import-linter checks the full layers contract)

```
interfaces/   (portal, api, backoffice{% if use_celery %}, tasks{% endif %})  → may import everything
domain/       (operations, queries, processes)                → may import data
data/         (models, constants, fields)                     → imports NOTHING above
```

### data/ — models are data containers
- Every model extends `{{ package_name }}.data.common.models.BaseModel` (UUID pk, created_at, updated_at).
  Exception: `User` extends `AbstractUser` directly (Django convention) — do not "fix" this.
- Enums as `TextChoices` in `constants.py` per app. No abbreviations. Spanish labels for user-facing text.
- NO business logic in models, NO signals, NO `save()` overrides for business rules.
- Custom User model: `{{ package_name }}.data.users.models.User` (`AUTH_USER_MODEL = "users.User"`).

### domain/ — Operations / Queries / Processes
- `operations.py`: ALL writes. Module-level functions, keyword-only args, `@transaction.atomic`.
  Every operation accepts `performed_by: User` and `action_source: str` and records audit via
  `{{ package_name }}.domain.auditlog.operations.record_audit(...)` in the same transaction.
  Raise domain exceptions, never HTTP errors.
- `queries.py`: ALL reads. Return QuerySet / instance / None / frozen dataclasses. Never raise, never mutate.
- `processes.py`: multi-step workflows coordinating operations + queries.
- No `**kwargs` mass assignment. >6 params → `@dataclass(frozen=True, slots=True)`.

### interfaces/ — thin presentation
- Portal views NEVER write to the ORM directly — call domain operations with
  `performed_by=request.user, action_source=ActionSource.PORTAL`.
- Portal auth: `@portal_login_required` decorator (separate from admin auth).
- HTMX: partial responses via Django 6.0 template partials (`{% raw %}{% partialdef %}{% endraw %}` /
  `render(request, "page.html#fragment")`). Form validation errors → 422.
- Admin classes live in `interfaces/backoffice/<context>/admin.py` — NEVER in data apps.
  `BackofficeConfig.ready()` autodiscovers them: a new context is just a package under
  `backoffice/` with an `admin.py`; no INSTALLED_APPS entry needed.
{% if use_api %}- API: django-ninja routers in `interfaces/api/`, Bearer token auth, catch domain exceptions → `HttpError`.
{% endif %}{% if use_celery %}- Celery tasks: thin wrappers in `interfaces/tasks/` calling domain ops. Idempotent, `acks_late`, time limits.
{% endif %}

## Conventions
- Import modules, not symbols: `from {{ package_name }}.apps.x import models` ✅ / `from ...models import Thing` ❌
- `from __future__ import annotations` in every module; full type annotations.
- No useless comments; docstrings only for business "why".
- Settings: `config/settings/{base,local,test,production}.py`; env via `.env` (django-environ).
- Tests: pytest markers `unit` (no DB) / `integration` (DB). Factories in `tests/factories/`. Never stash failing tests — fix immediately.

## Session end ("landing the plane")
1. Run quality gates: `uv run pytest && make lint`
2. Commit, then `git pull --rebase && git push` — work is NOT done until push succeeds.
